  <div data-page-zine="5">
    <h2>1.2 Infrastructure</h2>
    <p>
      Far more important to many counter-cultural figures than co-opting a
      mainstream aesthetic were co-opting expensive physical production
      resources—copy machines, printers, computers, paper, and other tools
      available freely at public institutions or in private companies, or at a
      price in copy shops.
    </p><p style="margin-block-end: auto;"
      >Nascent technology before the digital surveillance age allowed for this
      easily, as long as no toes were stepped on.
    </p>
  </div>
